Thailand injects 14 bln baht to help currency . Thailand ' s central bank said it injected 14 billion baht into the local money market on Friday to stabilise the national currency following fresh rumours of a possible devaluation . Governor Rerngchai Marakanond told reporters the central bank made the move earliy on Friday when domestic baht liquidity tightened in the wake of the devaluation rumours and a sharp slide in the Thai stock market . 
